(468, 27, 'description', 'I am a freelance writer in North Carolina, and I have been covering technology --including the technology in automobiles--since before Bill met Melinda or any of us met Google. I also write about education, parenting, family travel, and gardening. I currently write the Family Tech column in <em>Family Circle</em> magazine and Family Tech with Christina at FamilyCircle.com, and I blog on the Geek Girlfriends site. Clients--past and present--include <em>Better Homes and Gardens, Popular Science, This Old House Magazine, USA Weekend, PC Magazine, PC World,</em> Jaguar, Saks Fifth Avenue, and many others. I am thrilled to be a part of Jean Knows Cars.'),
