(486, 28, 'description', 'I''ve always had cars on the brain. I turned my first wrench when I was about four, growing up among my dad''s collection of weird old British and American classics. In adolescence, I was rifling through back issues of <em>Hot Rod</em> and <em>Car Craft, </em>clipping out photos and articles on fire-breathing hot rods. And after adopting my mom''s old Ford Escort, I started getting part-time jobs in garages, which sustained me all the way through college and grad school. I completed the restoration of my first car on student loans, and I currently own a total of four vintage vehicles, all of which I work on. Even after earning two academic degrees and toiling most of the way through a third, my heart remained in the garage, and just as my doctoral funding ran out, I got a break on a dream job that would allow me to combine my two major life passions: writing and cars. I''ve been writing about cars, covering motorsports and car shows, and having a ton of hell-raising adventures as an editor at CarDomain.com since 2007.'),
